column1: How many employees does your company or organization have?
column2: Do you know the options for mental health care available under your employer-provided coverage?
column3: Would you feel comfortable discussing a mental health disorder with your coworkers?
column4: Were you aware of the options for mental health care provided by your previous employers?
column5: Do you think that discussing a mental health disorder with previous employers would have negative consequences?
column6: Do you think that discussing a physical health issue with previous employers would have negative consequences?
column7: Would you have been willing to discuss a mental health issue with your direct supervisor(s)?
column8: Did you feel that your previous employers took mental health as seriously as physical health?
column9: Would you be willing to bring up a physical health issue with a potential employer in an interview?
column10: Do you think that team members/co-workers would view you more negatively if they knew you suffered from a mental health issue?
column11: Have you observed or experienced an unsupportive or badly handled response to a mental health issue in your current or previous workplace?
column12: Do you have a family history of mental illness?
column13: Do you currently have a mental health disorder?
column15: What country do you work in?
column17: Have you had mental health benefits before
column18: How easy is it to ask for mental health leave?
column19: Mental health effects on work when treated effectively
column20: Sharing mental health issue with family and friends
